quorum of the seventy april    th president of brigham young university–idaho in office august   – april   predecessor david a bednar successor clark gilbert personal details born  march   age  salt lake city utah alma mater harvard university ba ma phd spouses sue lorraine hunt clark children  biography portal   latterday saints portal kim bryce clark born march   is an american scholar educator and religious leader who has been a general authority of the church of jesus christ of latterday saints lds church since april  and the churchs seventeenth commissioner of church education since august  he served previously as the th president of brigham young university–idaho from  to  and as the dean of the harvard business school hbs from  to  where he was also the george f baker professor of business administration contents  early life and education  lds church service and family  awards  see also  references  further reading  external links early life and educationedit kim b clark was born on march   in salt lake city utah he and his family lived in salt lake city until  when his fathers new job required them to move to spokane washington clark matriculated at harvard university in  as a premed major and left after his freshman year to serve as a missionary for the lds church in germany following his mission clark enrolled for a time at brigham young university in  he resumed his studies at harvard where he received ba  ma  and phd  degrees in economics clark joined the harvard faculty in  and served as dean of the hbs from  to  as a professor at the hbs clarks research focused on modularity in design and the integration of technology and competition in industry evolution particularly within the computer industry he has published several articles in the harvard business review and other peerreviewed academic journals a few of his papers were coauthored with former hbs associate dean and former byuhawaii president steven c wheelwright in  clark left the hbs when lds church president gordon b hinckley appointed him president of byu–idaho on january   it was announced that effective april   clark would be succeeded by clark gilbert as the president of byu–idaho lds church service and familyedit clark has served in various assignments in the lds church including bishop scoutmaster elders quorum president sunday school teacher and counselor in a stake mission presidency from  to  clark served as an area seventy in the churchs idaho area on april   clark was sustained as a member of the first quorum of the seventy on august   he succeeded paul v johnson as the commissioner of church education clark and his wife sue have seven children awardsedit eagle scout award by the boy scouts of america distinguished eagle scout award by the national eagle scout association newcomenharvard award for best paper published in the business history review  see alsoedit list of general authorities of the church of jesus christ of latterday saints chronological listing of church commissioners of education referencesedit  httpwwwdeseretnewscomarticlefivenewgeneralauthoritiessustainedduringldschurchsgeneralconferencehtmlpgall  a b prescott marianne holman august   seminary and institute histories to be released church news   a b c faculty  research faculty hbsedu harvard business school retrieved   contribution ignored help  heaps julie dockstader october   president installed at byuidaho lds church news retrieved    a b inauguration byuiedu byu idaho retrieved   contribution ignored help  mower daniel october   news releases byuiedu byu idaho archived from the original on   contribution ignored help  clark gilbert announced as new president of byui ksl january    new general authorities young men presidency and primary presidency changes announced newsroom retrieved  april    a b distinguished eagle scout award pdf marketing  communication division boy scouts of america  retrieved   further readingedit halter jon c september  achievements and challenges s