he harvard business school to president of byuidaho kim b clark has had a career filled with pressures of one kind or another he describes a particularly stressful time one night i awoke from what must have been a nightmare i felt very anxious worried beset with strange thoughts and feelings of dread and darkness    i rolled out of bed onto my knees and asked heavenly father to help me    as i got up a phrase of scripture came into my mind it was just a fragment but it was the key i needed for we wrestle not against flesh and blood but against principalities against powers against the rulers of the darkness of this world    ephesians  the authors personal quest born that night to understand the armor of god became this thoughtprovoking and uniquely helpful book about the author kim b clark president kim b clark completed his freshman year at harvard university before serving a twoyear mission in the south german mission he then studied for one year at brigham young university where he met his wife sue they married in  and returned to cambridge where he completed his education at harvard universityearning bachelors masters and phd degrees in economics in  kim joined the harvard business school faculty he was named dean of the school in  he served in that capacity until summer  when he left to become the president of brigham young universityidaho kim and sue are the parents of seven children and the grandparents of nine view more products by kim b clark reviews average rating based upon one review a sleeper and a keeperby jana submitted on i bought this book on a huge sale so im assuming it was a sleeper i have loved reading the book it spoke to me even though my life experiences have been very different from the authors which denotes to me he is speaking with spirit its easy to be intimidated by president clark at first notice but he truly reveals himself weaknesses and all in the book and shows how we can be safe and progress in these latter days loved it write a re